== Cooking the Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 3cm chunks.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain well in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Cooking the Pork ==

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and pepper and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Building the Pilaf ==

Once the mince has browned, add the garlic and @chermoula spice mix{1} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} for the pork.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @peas{120%g} and @butter{20%g} through the cooked rice until piping hot and melted, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked rice and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} to the pan and stir to combine.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

== Serving ==

When ready, share the pork pilaf between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!